           <div type="translation" source="bib:Chhom2011_01"><!-- kuch: The term 'slave' should be understood as 'servant'. -->
 	<p n="1-13">Ruined. Among the <foreign>lvan</foreign> people, there are <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Phnos <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Jmas accompanied by a child 1, Tai Kaṁvrau accompanied by two children, Tai <gap reason="lost"/> accompanied by two children, another Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kansat accompanied by two children, Tai Kaṁvraḥ accompanied by two children, Tai <gap reason="lost"/> accompanied by four children, Tai Khñuṁ, Tai <gap reason="lost"/> accompanied by two children, Tai Kaṁvai accompanied by a child, Gho Chpoṅ, <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Saṁ-ap, Tai Kañj<gap reason="lost"/>, Tai <gap reason="lost"/>. Total: <gap reason="lost"/> male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied> <gap reason="lost"/>, 7 <supplied reason="subaudible">female slaves</supplied>, <gap reason="lost"/> children; grand total <gap reason="lost"/>.</p>
              <p n="14-24"><supplied reason="subaudible">Village of</supplied> Sthahe<gap reason="lost"/>, <gap reason="lost"/> Panda <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Thleṁ, Gho Kañci, Gho Kaṁvin, Gho Śivabhāva, Gho Kaṁvi, Gho Kañcan, Gvāl Nārāyana, Tai Thgan accompanied by a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>, Tai Kaṁvrau accompanied by a baby boy <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>, Tai Karppan accompanied by a daughter <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai rat</foreign></supplied>, Tai Śreṣṭha, Tai Bhājan accompanied by a baby <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si pau</foreign></supplied>, Tai Kanteṅ accompanied by a son <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>, Tai Thkep, Tai Cakcok, Tai Kañjir accompanied by a baby girl <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied>, another Tai Kanteṅ accompanied by a baby girl <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied>. Total: 8 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, an animal keeper <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, 10 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, two boys at the age of running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>si rat</foreign></supplied>, two girls at the age of running <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai rat</foreign></supplied>, two baby girls <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai pau</foreign></supplied>; grand total 26.</p>
              <p n="24-29">Village of Sthalā Vāp Pañ B: Si Kaṁpañ, Gho Prāna, Gho Chke, another Gho Chke, Gho Kanteṅ, Gho Pandan, Gho Kañci, another Gho Kañci, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Kanloñ, Gho Kan-i, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gvāl Kaṁvai, Gvāl Thge, Gvāl</p>
                   </div> 
